							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The main reason why I chose to be an alchemist was to make poison. So far, though, I've had nothing but trouble.  I'm currenly a lvl 16 rogue, 16 scholar. I made 20 unblemished poison viles (the highest grade), prestine liquid and npc bought suspention.  I cranked out  20 potions and didn't get a pristine potion once!!  <img src="images/smiles/icon_mad.gif" alt="Mad" border="0" />   grrrrr...  I'm wondering if it's a bug.  My chemistry (I  think that's the skill that gets raised from potion makin') is maxed at 82/82, my poison skill is 88/88 (something like that) The best quality poison I made con'd green to me w/ the "you are over qualified for this item." message.  I was trying to make one of the lvl 12 (easy) poisons... can't remember which one.
<br />

<br />
My question is, do prestine poisons have a higher skill requirement than the lower quality poisons of the type?
<br />

<br />
Since I can't seem to make poisons for my skill lvl,  does anyone know what the other potions do? I wish SOE would atleast add a discription of the potion after you used it. I made several potions w/ no clue as to what they did. Atlest you know it a poison (because it requires a poison vile *doh*)  I made a potion and drank it and got a message saying " You are not being attacked with crushing blow"   3 times over an 8 secound period. 
<br />
Am I wasting my time w/ Alchemy or is there a light at the end of the tunnel? 
<br />
Has anyone made a poison potion that matched their poison skill lvl and if so, what was the quality of comonates used ... etc. ?? (what  chemistry skill lvl, char poison lvl, char lvl etc. )
<br />
Sorry for all the questions.  Thanks for taking the time to read all this.<br />_________________<br />Niemals
<br />
