						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There is definitely a light at the end of the tunnel if you want to make money. Alchemy is a nearly self sufficent tradeskill (only relying on Jewellers for glassware 20+) and all its products are consumed when used, so theres an endless market. 
<br />

<br />
In time weapon, armor, etc crafters will hit a wall because 90% of their items are reusable and will eventually just build up in the market causing more supply then demand. WoW overcame this by making most crafted items single use, you had to bind it (attune in EQ2) and then it became untradeable and hence removed it from the economy. Also the other upside is as the game matures and peoples wealth increases they will look towards buying expensive single use items like food and potions.
<br />

<br />
But at the moment most people have just enough coin to feed themselves, pay room upkeep, mend and buy a few item upgrades. Stick with it poisons do get alot better in Tier 2, I nearly threw it in at 16-20 because most poisons were substandard compared to bought ones and the ones that were possibly good required rare materials. At level 22 I can already make poisons better then bought ones but of course they cost alot more due to having to buy the suspension from merchant. But its a good sign.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
