						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not a very good sign, crafted poisons aren't "that" much better then the ones you can buy from vendors.. if you look at it, the tier 5 poisons cost all of 9s or so from the vendors.. while crafting one requires a suspension that costs 92s..
<br />

<br />
No, making a poison at higher quality level dosen't increase the required skill on an item, or the mastery of that item as well..
<br />

<br />
As for comparing food to poisons/potions... shame on you!
<br />

<br />
Food is much easier to make since it just requires food harvests, which most people leave alone.. You only need Gathering and Fishing to work up a provisioner. Not only that, but you dont need many other things such as Oils, Washs, Resins, and Tempers that most other crafters need.. From what i've seen you also dont need many things from other crafters like Alchemist needs bottles and vials from jewelers..
<br />

<br />
Food is much MUCH cheaper to make without needing to buy insanely expensive solutions and suspensions, and easier to make considering the requirements.
<br />

<br />
Unlike poisons and potions, food is affected by the quality of the finished product.. and making an item pristine is pretty much no problem for an accomplished provisioner.
<br />

<br />
Foods will always be much cheaper to make then poisons unless they change something soon. Also..
<br />

<br />
Foods are much more in demand by other players, a good food and drink supply is pocket change compared to the prices people want for bank boxes, skills, jewelery, armor, weapons.. etc. They could pretty much name a price, if they wanted 50s for a stack of food, people would gladly pay it.
<br />

<br />
The food will last several hours granted, but with smart consumption.. you can make a stack of food and drink last for days. The regen benefits are awesome compared to the trivial effect of potions, or the vendor quality effects of poisons.
<br />

<br />
Not to mention that the most expensive food/drink you can buy is less potent then tier 1 crafted food/drink.. Making stuff that is much stronger then available through NPC merchants has it's own bonus there, as you become the primary source of it for the world.
<br />

<br />
If you wanted an easy to do tradeskill that would benefit both yourself and your friends, would get you a decent profit while not costing you too much, and didn't take all of your time invested into it.. Provisioner is that class. :p
<br />

<br />

<br />
So you know, I dream that some day they will wise up and make potions and poisons craft similar to throwing weapons, so they craft at 5, 10, 15, and 20 per attempt depending on quality of the success.. That way crafting a stack of poisons will just barely be cheaper and more effective then buying it from the vendor..
<br />

<br />
Think about it, if after all of the work you put into making a bunch of arrows.. that you only got 1 per crafting attempt, and it cost you close to 15s for that one crafting attempt, did you get your money's worth? :p</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
